## Install KVM & related packages:

```
sudo apt update
```

```
sudo apt install -y qemu-kvm libvirt-daemon-system libvirt-clients bridge-utils virtinst
```

```
sudo systemctl enable --now libvirtd
```

## Download Kali Linux ISO to VPS:

```
wget https://cdimage.kali.org/kali-rolling/amd64/iso/kali-linux-2025.1-installer-amd64.iso -O /var/lib/libvirt/kali.iso
```

## Create the Kali VM with VNC graphics for remote GUI access:

```
sudo virt-install \
--name kali-vm \
--ram 2048 \
--vcpus 2 \
--disk path=/var/lib/libvirt/images/kali-vm.img,size=20 \
--os-variant=debian10 \
--cdrom=/var/lib/libvirt/images/kali.iso \
--network network=default \
--graphics vnc,listen=0.0.0.0 \
--noautoconsole
```

## Manage VM lifecycle:

Start:
```
sudo virsh start kali-vm
```

Shutdown:
```
sudo virsh shutdown kali-vm
```

Delete VM:
```
sudo virsh undefine kali-vm --remove-all-storage
```
